            endo-beta-1,3-glucanase IV;
            endo-1,3-beta-D-glucanase;
            1,3-(1,3;1,4)-beta-D-glucan 3(4)-glucanohydrolase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Glycosylases;
            Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
SYSNAME     3(or 4)-beta-D-glucan 3(4)-glucanohydrolase
REACTION    Endohydrolysis of (1->3)- or (1->4)-linkages in beta-D-glucans when the glucose residue whose reducing group is involved in the linkage to be hydrolysed is itself substituted at C-3
COMMENT     Substrates include laminarin, lichenin and cereal D-glucans; different from EC 3.2.1.52 beta-N-acetylhexosaminidase.
HISTORY     EC 3.2.1.6 created 1961, modified 1976
